{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "SimCLR and BYOL pretraining have been investigated for the task of left ventricle segmentation.",
    "Saeed et al. [168] observed that SimCLR pretraining generally resulted in the best Dice score, but the difference was small across label availability fractions.",
    "Surprisingly, BYOL pretraining generally resulted in worse performance than full supervision.",
    "The results appeared to be consistent across two public datasets: EchoNet-Dynamic dataset [169] and CAMUS [170].",
    "To reduce redundancy of pretraining examples, they chose to use one randomly selected frame per clip during pretraining, despite using two labelled frames per clip for the downsteam task (one each for end-systole and end-diastole); it is possible that using more frames during pretraining may have improved performance."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
